# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation)
#   style    (formatting, no code change)
#   refactor (code change that doesn't fix bug or add feature)
#   test     (adding or updating tests)
#   chore    (maintenance)
#   perf     (performance improvement)
#   ci       (CI/CD changes)
#   build    (build system changes)
#   revert   (reverting changes)
#   design   (design system changes)
#   content  (content updates)
#   config   (configuration changes)
#   security (security fixes)
#   deps     (dependency updates)
#   auth     (authentication related)
#   payment  (payment/Stripe related)
#   coach    (coach-specific features)
#   client   (client-specific features)
#   admin    (admin panel features)
#   mobile   (mobile app specific)
#   ai       (AI/ML features)
#   analytics (analytics and tracking)
#
# Scope is optional but can be:
#   app, ui, components, pages, hooks, contexts, utils, lib, types,
#   auth, dashboard, intake, pricing, analytics, testing, mobile, ai,
#   api, db, build, deploy, config, deps, security,
#   tokens, atoms, molecules, organisms, templates, storybook,
#   tiers, subscriptions, coaching, nutrition, workouts, progress,
#   supabase, stripe, openai, capacitor, sentry
#
# Subject should:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
#   - Be no more than 100 characters
#   - Not end with a period
#
# Body should:
#   - Explain the "what" and "why" vs. "how"
#   - Use present tense
#   - Include motivation for change and contrast with previous behavior
#
# Footer should:
#   - Reference issues and PRs (e.g., "Closes #123", "Fixes #456")
#   - Note breaking changes with "BREAKING CHANGE:"
#
# Examples:
#   feat(auth): add OAuth2 authentication flow
#   fix(dashboard): resolve tier access control bug
#   docs(api): update authentication endpoint documentation
#   style(components): format button component with prettier
#   refactor(hooks): extract common data fetching logic
#   test(intake): add comprehensive form validation tests
#   chore(deps): update React to version 18.3.1
#   design(tokens): add new color palette for dark mode
#   security(auth): implement rate limiting for login attempts